FT  07 SEP 92 / The Farnborough Air Show: Two Gulfstream models announced
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
GULFSTREAM Aerospace of the US, builders of the market-leading G-IV business
jet, yesterday announced two models that direct its development thrust
squarely at the trans-Pacific market.
The Gulfstream V will have a non-stop range of 6,300 nautical miles, giving
it the capability of flying from New York to Tokyo or London to Singapore.
Gulfstream's second announcement was the replacement of the G-IV with the
G-IV-SP (Special Performance). The SP offers a 53 per cent improvement in
payload range performance over the G-IV.
Gulfstream emphasises that the SP is available now, while the G-V will be
ready for delivery in 1996.
Throughout next year, the company promises to sell the SP at the present
price of a G-IV: Dollars 23.5m. It quotes the price of a G-V as Dollars
29.5m in 1993 dollars. This price is without cabin outfitting, which adds
anything from Dollars 3m upwards to the price.
