<HEADLINE>
FT  05 SEP 92 / Markets: At a Glance - House prices fall again
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
House prices fell again in August according to the Nationwide and Halifax
price indices this week. Nationwide recorded a 0.2 per cent fall in prices
compared to the previous month, while Halifax found a 0.7 per cent fall. UK
house prices have fallen by over 5 per cent over the 12 months to August,
according to both indices.
Tim Melville-Ross, Nationwide's chief executive, said concern about the
economy was continuing to depress the market. The reintroduction last month
of stamp duty would 'act as a further brake on the market in the short
term,' he said. Halifax also had a gloomy prognosis, foreseeing no upturn in
the market this year and only muted recovery next, unless the economy
recovers.
