of the shareholding in AmBrit International.
Gross profit rose almost 50 per cent to Pounds 2.7m despite margins being
reduced from 42.4 to 37.5 per cent as a result of curtailed oil and gas
volumes and low product prices, and the temporary impact of high operating
costs inherited from recent communications acquisitions.
In communications, turnover more than doubled to Dollars 9m (Pounds 4.5m)
while gross profit doubled to Dollars 2.9m.
Earnings were 9.4p (7.19p) and the interim dividend is 3p on increased
capital (2.5p).
