<HEADLINE>
FT  04 SEP 92 / UK Company News: Pegasus to form joint venture
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pegasus Group, the USM-quoted computer software supplier, yesterday
announced plans to form a joint venture with the Deluxe Corporation of
Minnesota.
Under the terms of the deal Deluxe UK, a subsidiary of Deluxe Corporation,
will acquire 25 per cent of Stockforms, the computer forms and ancillary
products business which is a wholly owned subsidiary of Pegasus.
Deluxe will pay Pounds 1.71m cash for the stake, with an option to acquire
the remainder.
In the event that Deluxe exercises its option, Stockforms will pay
commissions to Pegasus for five years.
