of 29 cents compares with 27 cents in the previous year.
Amcor said the 'excellent' result was achieved in spite of severe recession
in Australia and its other main markets in New Zealand, Canada and Europe.
Activities outside Australia accounted for 35 per cent of sales and 23 per
cent of operating profits.
