bank with Lehman Brothers with the first. The next issue would be structured
'very much like the first Alps,' said Citibank.
Alps 1 was made up of five tranches: two public offerings consisting of
Dollars 208.4m fixed-rate bonds and Dollars 104.2m floating-rate notes, a
Dollars 70.4m private placement and two tranches of subordinated debt.
Mr Foley said that such instruments would help solve a capital shortage in
the airline industry.
They 'offer airlines the opportunity to uncouple from dependence on bank
debt . . . and widen the investor base to those who might not otherwise
invest in airlines'.
